               <floruit notBefore="1689" notAfter="1711">He was a governor of <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> who apprehended a rebel 
                  who had sought refuge in 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> among the Tulama <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</persName>. He was
                  a confidant of 
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> ʾIyāsu I</persName>
                  helping a plan attacks on <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</persName> and participating in his campaigns into 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName>. By the <date>1693</date>, he held the title of 
                  <persName ref="PRS3503Demetros">
                     <roleName type="title">ṣahafe lam</roleName>
                  </persName>; 
                  he was also <persName ref="PRS3503Demetros">
                     <roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName>
                  </persName>. By the end of the decade, however,  he had lost a favour at the court. But 
                  he had regained the governorship of <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName>, and from mid <date>1709</date> to mid 
                  <date>1711</date> he held the position of <persName ref="PRS3503Demetros">
                     <roleName type="title">rās</roleName>
                  </persName> under <persName ref="PRS9449Tewoflos"/>
                  </floruit>
                  
               </person>
